to give us a lift home.

552
00:21:28.166 --> 00:21:29.559
Let's lock and load.

553
00:21:29.583 --> 00:21:31.726
I'll be there
in a minute. Mr. B.

554
00:21:31.750 --> 00:21:33.875
(birds singing )

555
00:21:36.583 --> 00:21:38.976
KIM:
Pretty amazing.

556
00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:40.559
What do you mean?
Everything.

557
00:21:40.583 --> 00:21:41.726
You were awesome.

558
00:21:41.750 --> 00:21:43.101
Yeah.

559
00:21:43.125 --> 00:21:44.851
This is the one place
where I know the score.

560
00:21:44.875 --> 00:21:47.142
Where Ron Stoppable
knows what it takes

561
00:21:47.166 --> 00:21:48.559
to be the last camper standing.

562
00:21:48.583 --> 00:21:51.101
(board creaking )
Yikes!

563
00:21:51.125 --> 00:21:52.309
Ron. the stuff you did...

564
00:21:52.333 --> 00:21:53.392
You were resourceful.

565
00:21:53.416 --> 00:21:54.684
You were brave.

566
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:56.267
That doesn't have anything
to do with this place.

567
00:21:56.291 --> 00:21:57.434
It'syou.

568
00:21:57.458 --> 00:21:58.559
You think so?

569
00:21:58.583 --> 00:22:00.434
Mm-hmm.

570
00:22:00.458 --> 00:22:02.392
So. on our
next mission. I
call the shots?

571
00:22:02.416 --> 00:22:03.601
Uh... we'll see.

572
00:22:03.625 --> 00:22:04.684
Oh. come on.

573
00:22:04.708 --> 00:22:06.267
I know what that means.

574
00:22:06.291 --> 00:22:07.851
It means. we'll see.

575
00:22:07.875 --> 00:22:10.309
Yeah. that's a code
for "not a chance."

576
00:22:10.333 --> 00:22:12.684
Actually. it's code for
"ferociously unlikely."

577
00:22:12.708 --> 00:22:14.833
Oh. man.

